version_description: This is a "Bluesy Swing" version of Sting's "English Man In New York". You can listen this version here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5MhoXWvgOqA.

This is a chord version that is meant to help novice players. The chords are simplified and are now only open chords. Some minor timing changes has been made compared to the other versions. The entire song now also have chords above the lyrics to help users with auto scroll.
I'm not sure at all about these chords, but I think they work. Thanks :).
Easier to play with a capo on 2 and other versions had some notes in the wrong places (or missing).
Complete chords with intro and outro / tab for main pattern / suggestions for playable voicings of special chords.
